early shearing
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:the shearing of sheep in which fleecewool yolk has not risen.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:sticky shearing
