Date: 0/0/1955
Source: Wool Away!
Author: BOWEN
Vol / Page: 76
Edition:
Quote: On lamb shearing, crutching, early or sticky shearing, no lead is put on, as it is essential that this type of wool be cut as soon as the comb enters the wool.
